This PR adds support for specifying raw content as part of the `purge` config, mimicking [the PurgeCSS API](https://purgecss.com/configuration.html#options):

```js
module.exports = {
  purge: [
    './src/**/*.html',
    { raw: '<div class="bg-red-500"></div>' },
  ],
}
```

You can also specify an extension which is used to select the appropriate extractor:

```js
module.exports = {
  purge: {
    content: [
      {
        raw: '<div class="bg-red-500"></div>',
        extension: 'html',
      },
    ],
    options: {
      extractors: [
        {
          extractor: (content) => { /* ... */ },
          extensions: ['html'],
        },
      ],
    },
  },
}
```

